{{punctuation marks}}
==Translingual==

===Symbol===
'''!'''

# A symbol used to denote [[excitement]], [[surprise]] or [[shock]].
#: ''Run for your lives'''!'''''
# {{cattag|computing}} In some contexts, it represents a [[Boolean]] ''not''.
#: ''If '''!'''x''
#: "if '''not''' x"
# {{cattag|computing}} In [[e-mail]] messaging, it represents a separator for an [[e-mail address]].
# {{cattag|mathematics}} [[factorial]]
#: ''5'''!'''''
#: "five '''factorial'''"
# {{cattag|chess}} a good move

===Usage notes===
* It's name is variously [[exclamation mark]], [[exclamation point]] or, in computing contexts, [[shriek]] or [[bang]]

[[Image:Bang.svg|30px|thumb|An exclamation mark]]
